<p>So because some silly warrior didn't see the wisdom in asking for your help, you decided that you would make sure he died so you could steal the kill.  Killing two birds with one stone... not sharing the spawn, and paying back the ignorant warrior who dared to try to solo a mob several levels below him... that about sum it up? <br /> <br />You could have snared the mob, feared it and finished it with the warrior at your side.  Demonstrating superior ranger tactics and capability - without being spiteful or vindictive.  Hey you might still have outdamaged the warrior and taken the kill, but at that point the warrior had already said uncle. <br /> <br />While I could quite easily see myself acting similarly under your circumstances in the heat of the moment, in retrospect I would not have been proud of it... and I doubt I would have been so excited about the event that I felt i had to share it with the rest of the world. <br /> <br />I'm sure the warrior didnt try to solo matar again without help.  You had an opportunity to make an ally that day.  Eventually you will need a warrior as much as the warrior needed you. <br /> <br />Gladstone <br /> <br />49 Warrior <br />30 Druid <br />24 Bard <br /> <br /></p>
